The Governor of Edo State, Mr. Godwin Nogheghase Obaseki has condoled the Edo State governorship candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in 2017, Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu over the death of his brother, Osato Ize-Iyamu. In a condolence letter he personally signed, the Edo State governor described Osato as “a man of ideas, a liberal democrat and a man of peace,” adding that “those who have known him for decades attest to these rare and sterling qualities of his”. “His passing is a huge loss to all of us. He will be sorely missed and I urge you to find comfort in the reassuring promise of God that we will all meet in the morning of resurrection day. Please be strong and do accept my sincere and heartfelt condolences. I commiserate with you and the entire members of the Ize-Iyamu family in these trying times,” Obaseki added.